## cuda
https://developer.nvidia.com/cuda-downloads
Follow instructions, add all .debs before installing.

## install cudnn
https://developer.nvidia.com/rdp/cudnn-download
https://docs.nvidia.com/deeplearning/sdk/cudnn-install/index.html#installlinux-tar

## chrome
https://www.google.com/chrome/
sudo dpkg -i google-chrome-stable_current_amd64.deb
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install google-chrome-stable

## bunch of programs
sudo apt-get install terminator silversearcher-ag vim texlive-full texmaker tmux htop meld ninja-build ffmpeg vlc dconf-tools unclutter

## remap caps-lock to ctrl
Run dconf-editor
Navigate to org.gnome.desktop.input-sources
Set xkb-options to ['ctrl:nocaps']

## fish
sudo apt-add-repository ppa:fish-shell/release-2
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install fish

We can't set the default shell with `chsh`, since we are using LDAP.
But the dotfiles should enable fish in Terminator and tmux.

## vim
mkdir ~/.vim
git clone https://github.com/flazz/vim-colorschemes.git ~/.vim

## powerline
sudo apt-get install fonts-powerline
sudo apt-get install powerline python3-powerline

It may be necessary to modify the argument order in the fish bindings file manually.
/usr/share/powerline/bindings/fish/powerline-setup.fish
https://groups.google.com/forum/#!topic/powerline-support/m94nK0Bmg28

## ssh
Add keys to ~/.ssh/
If server, add public key to ~/.ssh/authorized_keys

